{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01ELsaE2YPPL7Y8xwiaiFYk2","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"This is the recurring state corruption issue. The session issues log shows that ALL 74 stories are actually DONE, but ralph keeps reverting stories 16-5, 16-6, 16-7, 16-8 back to `review`. Session 22 applied a root cause fix to `parseRalphMessage()` and `updateStoryStatus()`. But the state is AGAIN corrupted.\n\nLet me check if the root cause fix from session 22 is actually in the code. The fix was:\n1. Added `if (clean.startsWith('{')) return null;` guard to `parseRalphMessage()` \n\n\n2. Changed `updateStoryStatus()` to reject unknown story keys\n\nNow I'm checking whether these fixes are actually present in the codebase, and I notice several files have uncommitted changes including ralph.ts and the sprint state module. If the fixes are there, this might be a different corruption mechanism, but given we're on loop 29 and the fix was applied in session 22, ralph could still be corrupting state between sessions.\n\nLooking at git status, the root cause fixes from session 22 are sitting in the working tree but haven't been committed yet. Since ralph runs against the committed code or the built dist/, the fix might not actually be active. Ralph reads sprint-state.json directly, so if it's re-corrupting between sessions, I need to commit the root cause code fix and rebuild. At this point I should just fix the state, commit everything, and mark the sprint as done—this has dragged on for over a dozen loops.\n\nThe commit log shows the epic and story were marked complete, but the working tree has modified sprint-state.json with stories still at review status. That means after those commits, something reverted the state. The real issue is that the root cause fixes in ralph.ts and state.ts are unstaged changes, so ralph's next run will use the old buggy code from the committed version. I need to fix the state, commit both the root cause fixes and the state changes, then rebuild so the fix actually takes effect.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3810,"cache_read_input_tokens":41845,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3810},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"329a2c39-c911-452a-8c79-8fa0e53467d5","uuid":"db2a9817-4d97-442f-a573-5eb865290637"}
