{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01MsSNN8Vj1Z8bzhRzDEQb55","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Retrospective written to `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/session-retro-2026-03-27.md`.\n\n**Summary of what was done:**\n- Read the session issues log (sessions 16-29), sprint status, and existing retro\n- Ran `codeharness stats --save` — total project cost is $667.12 across 4,931 API calls\n- Appended session 29 retrospective with `---` separator\n\n**Key findings in the retrospective:**\n- The root cause fix from session 22 was never committed — ralph runs from built code, so the fix was dead for 7 sessions\n- Estimated waste from 13 state corruption sessions: **$38-49** (5.7-7.3% of project budget)\n- Phantom `1-1-foo` is the 5th most expensive \"story\" at $13.79 — all wasted\n- `sprint-state.json` was the most re-read file across sessions (3-4x per session due to external modification)\n- Sessions 16, 17, 19, 20, 23-28 were entirely redundant — same manual fix repeated\n- 3 new action items added: pre-session `git diff --stat` check, post-fix commit enforcement, sprint-status.yaml regeneration"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: ae02a52ab64a0c8a0 (use SendMessage with to: 'ae02a52ab64a0c8a0' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 30893\ntool_uses: 9\nduration_ms: 113764</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"329a2c39-c911-452a-8c79-8fa0e53467d5","uuid":"6a99ce36-a6c0-4006-9860-00dbd538b488","timestamp":"2026-03-27T15:26:29.808Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /retrospective for the current sprint session.\n\nSprint status: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/sprint-status.yaml\nSession issues log: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md\nCost report: Run `codeharness stats --save` to get token consumption data. Read `_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/cost-report.md` and include cost analysis in the retrospective.\n\nCRITICAL: Read the session issues log FIRST. This file contains real problems, workarounds, bugs, and observations reported by every subagent that ran this session. These are the raw materials for your retrospective — do not ignore them.\n\nCRITICAL: Run `codeharness stats --save` to generate the cost report. Read `_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/cost-report.md` and include cost analysis in the retrospective.\n\nCRITICAL: The session issues log contains `## Token Report` sections from each subagent. Aggregate these to understand WHERE tokens were spent inside subagents (not just the parent). Look for:\n- Which subagent phases had the most tool calls?\n- Which subagents read the same files repeatedly?\n- Which Bash commands produced the largest outputs?\n- What redundant operations were reported?\nInclude this subagent-level breakdown in the cost analysis section.\n\nContext for this session (#29):\n- All 74 stories across 16 epics are DONE\n- This session fixed state corruption for the 13th time\n- The KEY action was COMMITTING the root cause fix from session 22 that was never committed\n- Root cause: parseRalphMessage() matched story patterns in JSON lines, creating phantoms\n- Secondary fix: updateStoryStatus() now rejects unknown story keys\n- The uncommitted fix was the reason ralph kept corrupting state across sessions 22-28\n- 152 test suites (4018 tests) pass, build clean\n\nProduce a retrospective that covers:\n1. **Session summary** — which stories were attempted, their outcomes, time spent\n2. **Issues analysis** — categorize and analyze all issues from the session log\n3. **Cost analysis** — from the cost report\n4. **What went well** — root cause identified and committed\n5. **What went wrong** — 13 sessions wasted on same bug because fix wasn't committed\n6. **Lessons learned** — always commit fixes immediately, never leave code changes uncommitted\n7. **Action items** — concrete next steps\n\nWrite the retrospective to _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/session-retro-2026-03-27.md. Since a retro for today already exists, append to it with a `---` separator and timestamp.\n\nDo NOT ask the user any questions — proceed autonomously.\nDo NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.","agentId":"ae02a52ab64a0c8a0","agentType":"general-purpose","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Retrospective written to `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/session-retro-2026-03-27.md`.\n\n**Summary of what was done:**\n- Read the session issues log (sessions 16-29), sprint status, and existing retro\n- Ran `codeharness stats --save` — total project cost is $667.12 across 4,931 API calls\n- Appended session 29 retrospective with `---` separator\n\n**Key findings in the retrospective:**\n- The root cause fix from session 22 was never committed — ralph runs from built code, so the fix was dead for 7 sessions\n- Estimated waste from 13 state corruption sessions: **$38-49** (5.7-7.3% of project budget)\n- Phantom `1-1-foo` is the 5th most expensive \"story\" at $13.79 — all wasted\n- `sprint-state.json` was the most re-read file across sessions (3-4x per session due to external modification)\n- Sessions 16, 17, 19, 20, 23-28 were entirely redundant — same manual fix repeated\n- 3 new action items added: pre-session `git diff --stat` check, post-fix commit enforcement, sprint-status.yaml regeneration"}],"totalDurationMs":113764,"totalTokens":30893,"totalToolUseCount":9,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3153,"cache_read_input_tokens":27420,"output_tokens":319,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":3153},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
